<footer>Timothy Brown, who had leukemia and HIV, in San Francisco, Nov. 2, 2011. After receiving two bone marrow transplants to treat Brown's leukemia, HIV could no longer be detected in his body. Brown's experience and that of another patient has given scientists hope that a cure for AIDS may be achievable.<br>(HEIDI SCHUMANN/NYT)</footer>
